subject: CS 150: Unit Three - Resources
body:
Hello CS 150 Student

After reviewing the exam and other content in the course, we noticed students are not yet meeting expectations in certain topic areas. Do not worry, these are challenging topics, and it is completely fine to not understand them the first time around. However, in order to prepare students for the next exam we wanted to provide some resources to improve understanding of the content. Please remember, programming is like music; you need to practice to become successful at it.

Please note, these are third party resources selected by the TAs and other students. You should not sign up for anything, and none of this is required work! It is simply a third party option to present the topic in a different manner. These are intentionally not in a set order. As such, it is alright to find a resource not to your liking and quickly move to the next one. If you find it useful, we encourage you to return to that resource.

Here are some topics we encourage students to work on:

Fundamentals - Operations/Syntax

Here are some resources for you to look at fundamental java concepts.
